metadata.name: I Can't Seem To Let Go
metadata.description:
These muses might turn into other things.

Or not.

This is Muse 1 - I Can't Seem To Let Go. Sometimes I feel so much resistance to do the things I need to do most that it's paralyzing. When that happens, I notice I'll try to do anything that feels nostalgic to help break through the resistance.

Through conversations with my community, my current thought is to release these muses as open editions for 0.01 ETH, and close them when I drop the next muse. It could be a week, a month -- not really putting an expected frequency on it.

Mint an edition: https://app.manifold.xyz/c/i-cant-seem-to-let-go

View all of the muses: https://www.mikebassmusic.com/muses

Owners of this NFT may request the audio and cover art files. Ownership and copyright of the music and lyrics remains with Mike Bass.
